title: Untitled
Defunciones menor de seis años por fecha
content:
library(tidyverse)
library(magrittr, include.only = "%<>%")

# Se debe descargar y descomprimir dos archivos:
# - Defunciones Oficiales de 1990 a 2020:
#   Link: https://repositoriodeis.minsal.cl/DatosAbiertos/VITALES/DEFUNCIONES_FUENTE_DEIS_1990_2020_CIFRAS_OFICIALES.zip
# - Defunciones Preliminares de 2021 a la fecha:
#   Link: https://repositoriodeis.minsal.cl/DatosAbiertos/VITALES/DEFUNCIONES_FUENTE_DEIS_2021_2023_28112023.zip
 
# Link a la ruta de las defunciones oficiales.
# Se filtra el archivo para que no ocupe mucho peso en la memoria.
ruta1 <- "~/../Downloads/DEFUNCIONES_FUENTE_DEIS_1990_2020_CIFRAS_OFICIALES/DEFUNCIONES_FUENTE_DEIS_1990_2020_CIFRAS_OFICIALES.csv"
defunciones_deis <- read_delim(ruta1, delim = ";", escape_double = FALSE,
                               col_names = FALSE, locale=locale(encoding = "ISO-8859-1"),
                               trim_ws = TRUE) %>%
  filter(X5 <= 6)

# Link a la ruta de las defunciones preliminares. Las filas se añaden a la base
# de datos usando add_row.
ruta2 <- "~/../Downloads/DEFUNCIONES_FUENTE_DEIS_2021_2023_28112023/DEFUNCIONES_FUENTE_DEIS_2021_2023_28112023.csv"
defunciones_deis %<>%
  add_row(
    read_delim(ruta2, delim = ";", escape_double = FALSE,
               col_names = FALSE, locale=locale(encoding = "ISO-8859-1"),
               trim_ws = TRUE)
  )

names(defunciones_deis) <- c("ANO_DEF", "FECHA_DEF", "GLOSA_SEXO", "EDAD_TIPO", "EDAD_CANT",
                             "CODIGO_COMUNA_RESIDENCIA", "GLOSA_COMUNA_RESIDENCIA",
                             "GLOSA_REG_RES", "DIAG1", "CAPITULO_DIAG1", "GLOSA_CAPITULO_DIAG1",
                             "CODIGO_GRUPO_DIAG1", "GLOSA_GRUPO_DIAG1", "CODIGO_CATEGORIA_DIAG1",
                             "GLOSA_CATEGORIA_DIAG1", "CODIGO_SUBCATEGORIA_DIAG1",
                             "GLOSA_SUBCATEGORIA_DIAG1", "DIAG2", "CAPITULO_DIAG2",
                             "GLOSA_CAPITULO_DIAG2", "CODIGO_GRUPO_DIAG2", "GLOSA_GRUPO_DIAG2",
                             "CODIGO_CATEGORIA_DIAG2", "GLOSA_CATEGORIA_DIAG2", "CODIGO_SUBCATEGORIA_DIAG2",
                             "GLOSA_SUBCATEGORIA_DIAG2", "LUGAR_DEFUNCION")
defunciones_deis %<>%
  filter(EDAD_CANT <= 6) %>%
  group_by(FECHA_DEF) %>%
  count()



defunciones_deis %>%
  ggplot() +
  aes(x=FECHA_DEF, y=n) +
  geom_jitter(alpha=.1) +
  geom_smooth() +
  labs(title="Defunciones de niños y niñas menores de 6 años",
       x="Fecha",
       y="Número de defunciones",
       caption="Autor: Andrés Necochea\n
                Fuente: Elaboración propia en base a datos de DEIS\n
                Nota: Datos a partir de 2021 son preliminares")

title: Carrot Farm "Cyclical"
content:
x = 0
y = 9
c = 0
 
term.setTextColor(colors.orange)
print("Starting Operation...")
 
 
while true do
function refuel()
    
    if turtle.getFuelLevel() < 500 then
        turtle.select(16)
        turtle.placeUp()
        turtle.suckUp()
        turtle.refuel()
        turtle.dropUp()
        turtle.digUp()
        turtle.select(1)
    end
end
 
function base(c)
 
refuel()
for frente=1,10 do
    turtle.forward()
end
    turtle.turnLeft()
for frente2=1,11 do
    turtle.forward()
end
    turtle.turnLeft()
    
c = 0
print("Base Reached...")
print("Deploying Items...")
        if turtle.getItemCount(1) > 1 then
    turtle.select(15)
    turtle.placeUp()
for drop=1,14 do
    turtle.select(drop)
    turtle.dropUp()
    end
turtle.select(15)
turtle.digUp()
turtle.select(1)
end
 term.setTextColor(colors.cyan)
print("Entering StandBy Mode...")
sleep(150)
term.clear()
term.setCursorPos(0,0)
term.setTextColor(colors.yellow)
print("Five Minutes Elapsed...")
print("Restarting Operation...")
end
 
function turnAround(colunas)
 
    if (colunas%2) == 0 then
    turtle.turnRight()
    turtle.forward()
    turtle.turnRight()
    else
    turtle.turnLeft()
    turtle.forward()
    turtle.turnLeft()
    end 
end
 
for colunas=1,11 do
refuel()
c= c+1
for frente=x+1,10 do
    x= x+1
    turtle.forward()
    local harvest, data = turtle.inspectDown()
        if harvest == true then
            if data.state.age == 7 then
                turtle.select(1)
                turtle.digDown()
                turtle.placeDown()
             end
        end
    end
if x == 10 then
x = 0
end
turnAround(colunas)
end
if c == 11 then
    base(c)
end
term.setTextColor(colors.lime)
print("Work Done...")
term.setTextColor(colors.purple)
print("Returning to Base...")
end

title: ME auslesen automatisierung
content:
os.loadAPI("ocs/apis/sensor")
sen = sensor.wrap("top")

print("Welche Seite wird erstellt: ")
print("1-9 sind möglich")
term.setTextColor(colors.red)
local Page = tonumber(io.read())
term.setTextColor(colors.lime)
print("gespeichert")

local function extendProgramWithItems(page)
    local REQUEST_IDS = {
        -- Hier kannst du weitere IDs hinzufügen, wenn das Programm erweitert wird
    }

    while true do
        s = sen.getTargets()

        function getS()
            for v, k in pairs(s) do
                if k.Name == "ME Wireless Access Point" then   
                    target = v
                end
            end
            return target
        end

        f = getS()
        s1 = sen.getTargetDetails(target)

        for _, item in pairs(s1.Items) do
            term.setTextColor(colors.lightBlue)
            io.write("Bitte Item-ID von ")
            term.setTextColor(colors.red)
            io.write(item.Name)
            term.setTextColor(colors.lightBlue)
            io.write(" eingeben: ")
            local ID = tonumber(io.read())
            term.setTextColor(colors.lime)
            print("gespeichert")

            -- Erstellen der Einträge für REQUEST_IDS basierend auf der Eingabe
            local entry = {}
            entry[item.Name:gsub("%s+", "") .. ":0"] = ID -- Wenn kein Doppelpunkt im Namen vorhanden ist, wird ":0" verwendet
            REQUEST_IDS[#REQUEST_IDS + 1] = entry
        end
        
        sleep(0.5)
    end

    -- Hier wird die neue Funktion erstellt und die abgefragten Items eingefügt
    local function generatedFunction()
        -- Iteriere durch REQUEST_IDS und füge die abgefragten Items in die Funktion ein
        for _, entry in ipairs(REQUEST_IDS) do
            for itemName, itemID in pairs(entry) do
                print("Füge Item " .. itemName .. " mit ID " .. itemID .. " hinzu")
                -- Hier könntest du die Aktionen für jedes abgefragte Item einfügen
            end
        end
    end

    -- Rückgabe der generierten Funktion
    return generatedFunction
end

-- Aufruf der Funktion, um das Programm zu erweitern und die generierte Funktion zu erhalten
local newFunction = extendProgramWithItems(Page)

-- Jetzt hast du die generierte Funktion "newFunction", die die abgefragten Items enthält
-- Du kannst sie aufrufen, um die Aktionen für die abgefragten Items auszuführen
newFunction()

def processline(line):
    mins = []
    maxs = []

    mins.append( int(min([i for i in range(len(line)) if line.startswith(("zero","0"), i)], default="99")) )
    maxs.append( int(max([i for i in range(len(line)) if line.startswith(("zero","0"), i)], default="-1")) )

    mins.append( int(min([i for i in range(len(line)) if line.startswith(("one","1"), i)], default="99")) )
    maxs.append( int(max([i for i in range(len(line)) if line.startswith(("one","1"), i)], default="-1")) )
    
    mins.append( int(min([i for i in range(len(line)) if line.startswith(("two","2"), i)], default="99")) )
    maxs.append( int(max([i for i in range(len(line)) if line.startswith(("two","2"), i)], default="-1")) )

    mins.append( int(min([i for i in range(len(line)) if line.startswith(("three","3"), i)], default="99")) )
    maxs.append( int(max([i for i in range(len(line)) if line.startswith(("three","3"), i)], default="-1")) )

    mins.append( int(min([i for i in range(len(line)) if line.startswith(("four","4"), i)], default="99")) )
    maxs.append( int(max([i for i in range(len(line)) if line.startswith(("four","4"), i)], default="-1")) )

    mins.append( int(min([i for i in range(len(line)) if line.startswith(("five","5"), i)], default="99")) )
    maxs.append( int(max([i for i in range(len(line)) if line.startswith(("five","5"), i)], default="-1")) )

    mins.append( int(min([i for i in range(len(line)) if line.startswith(("six","6"), i)], default="99")) )
    maxs.append( int(max([i for i in range(len(line)) if line.startswith(("six","6"), i)], default="-1")) )

    mins.append( int(min([i for i in range(len(line)) if line.startswith(("seven","7"), i)], default="99")) )
    maxs.append( int(max([i for i in range(len(line)) if line.startswith(("seven","7"), i)], default="-1")) )

    mins.append( int(min([i for i in range(len(line)) if line.startswith(("eight","8"), i)], default="99")) )
    maxs.append( int(max([i for i in range(len(line)) if line.startswith(("eight","8"), i)], default="-1")) )

    mins.append( int(min([i for i in range(len(line)) if line.startswith(("nine","9"), i)], default="99")) )
    maxs.append( int(max([i for i in range(len(line)) if line.startswith(("nine","9"), i)], default="-1")) )

    return int(str(mins.index(min(mins)))+str(maxs.index(max(maxs))))

def calibrate():
    file = open("input.txt","r")
    lines = file.readlines()
    total = 0
    for line in lines:
        total += processline(line)
    
    print(total)


if __name__ == '__main__':
    calibrate()

json="${infile%.txt}.json"

title: 7.1 surround peace preset generator
content:
# 7.1 surround sound peace equalizer preset generator
# Made by AyPeeEye in collaboration with ChatGPT

import tkinter as tk
from tkinter import filedialog

# Function to read EQ file
def parse_eq_file(file_path):
    filters = {}  # Dictionary to store filter information for each channel

    with open(file_path, 'r') as file:
        lines = file.readlines()

        # Logic to identify the EQ file format and parse the filters
        if 'Filter Settings file' in lines[0]:  # Example condition to detect REW format
            channel_filters = {}  # Dictionary to store filter info for a single channel

            for line in lines:
                if line.startswith('Filter'):
                    filter_info = line.split()

                    if filter_info[2] == 'ON':
                        if filter_info[3] != 'None':
                            if filter_info[8] != 0:
                                filter_type = filter_info[3]  # Extracting filter type
                                frequency = filter_info[5]  # Extracting frequency
                                gain = filter_info[8]  # Extracting gain
                                q_value = filter_info[11]  # Extracting Q value
                                
                                filter_number = int(filter_info[1][:-1])  # Extracting the filter number
                                channel_filters[filter_number] = {
                                    'FilterType': filter_type,
                                    'Frequency': frequency,
                                    'Gain': gain,
                                    'QValue': q_value
                                }
            
            filters = channel_filters  # Store the parsed filter data
        
        elif 'Preamp' in lines[0]:  # Example condition to detect squig.link format
            channel_filters = {}  # Dictionary to store filter info for a single channel

            for line in lines:
                if line.startswith('Filter'):
                    filter_info = line.split()

                    if filter_info[2] == 'ON':
                        if filter_info[8] != 0:
                            filter_type = filter_info[3]
                            frequency = filter_info[5]
                            gain = filter_info[8]
                            q_value = filter_info[11]
                            
                            # Checking for both shelf filter types
                            if filter_type in ['LSQ', 'LSC', 'HSQ', 'HSC']:
                                filter_type = 'LSQ' if filter_type in ['LSQ', 'LSC'] else 'HSQ'
                                
                            filter_number = int(filter_info[1][:-1])  # Extracting the filter number
                            channel_filters[filter_number] = {
                                'FilterType': filter_type,
                                'Frequency': frequency,
                                'Gain': gain,
                                'QValue': q_value
                            }
            
            filters = channel_filters  # Store the parsed filter data
    
    return filters

# Function to create and write to a peace preset output file
def generate_peace_file(file_paths, output_filename, description_comment):
    # Parse each EQ file and store the filter information
    channel_names = ["All", "Left", "Right", "Center", "Subwoofer", "Left Rear", "Right Rear", "Left Side", "Right Side"]
    parsed_data = {}

    for idx, path in enumerate(file_paths):
        channel_name = channel_names[idx]
        if path != "None":
            parsed_data[channel_name] = parse_eq_file(path)
        else:
            parsed_data[channel_name] = "None"

    # Dictionary to store the preamp values for each channel
    preamp_values = {}

    # Iterate through each channel's filters
    for channel_name in channel_names:
        if parsed_data[channel_name] == "None":
            continue
        else:
            filters_data = parsed_data[channel_name]

            # Find the maximum positive gain for the current channel
            positive_gains = [float(filter_info['Gain']) for filter_info in filters_data.values() if float(filter_info['Gain']) > 0]
            max_channel_gain = max(positive_gains) if positive_gains else 0
            
            # Set the preamp value for the channel based on the maximum positive gain
            preamp_value = -1 * max_channel_gain if max_channel_gain > 0 else 0
            preamp_values[channel_name] = preamp_value
        
    # Generate content for the .peace file based on parsed data
    content = ""
    # Add content for General section
    content += "[General]\nDescription=" + description_comment + "\n"
    for idx, channel_name in enumerate(channel_names):
        if parsed_data[channel_name] != "None":
            if idx == 0:
                content += f"PreAmp={preamp_values[channel_name]}\n"
            else:
                content += f"PreAmp{idx}={preamp_values[channel_name]}\n"

    # Add content for Speakers section
    content += "[Speakers]\n"
    speaker_names = ["all", "L", "R", "C", "SUB", "RL", "RR", "SL", "SR"]
    for i, channel_name in enumerate(channel_names):
        content += f"SpeakerId{i}={i}\n"
        content += f"SpeakerTargets{i}={speaker_names[i]}\n"
        content += f"SpeakerName{i}={channel_name}\n"  # Use channel_name here
    
    # Add content for Frequencies, Gains, Qualities, and Filters sections
    for i, channel_name in enumerate(channel_names):
        if parsed_data[channel_name] != "None":
            filters_data = parsed_data[channel_name]
            # Create a mapping dictionary for filter types
            filter_type_mapping = {'PK': '', 'LSQ': '14', 'HSQ': '15'}
            non_pk_filters_exist = any(filter_info['FilterType'] != 'PK' for filter_info in filters_data.values())
        
            # All channel
            if i == 0:
                content += "[Frequencies]\n"
                content += '\n'.join([f"Frequency{j}={filters_data[j]['Frequency']}" for j in range(1, len(filters_data) + 1)]) + '\n'
                
                content += "[Gains]\n"
                content += '\n'.join([f"Gain{j}={filters_data[j]['Gain']}" for j in range(1, len(filters_data) + 1)]) + '\n'
                
                content += "[Qualities]\n"
                content += '\n'.join([f"Quality{j}={filters_data[j]['QValue']}" for j in range(1, len(filters_data) + 1)]) + '\n'
                
                if non_pk_filters_exist:
                    content += "[Filters]\n"
                    filters_not_pk = [f"Filter{j}={filter_type_mapping[filters_data[j]['FilterType']]}" for j in range(1, len(filters_data) + 1) if filters_data[j]['FilterType'] != 'PK']
                    content += '\n'.join(filters_not_pk) + '\n'
                
            # Other 8 channels
            else:
                content += f"[Frequencies{i}]\n"
                content += '\n'.join([f"Frequency{j}={filters_data[j]['Frequency']}" for j in range(1, len(filters_data) + 1)]) + '\n'
            
                content += f"[Gains{i}]\n"
                content += '\n'.join([f"Gain{j}={filters_data[j]['Gain']}" for j in range(1, len(filters_data) + 1)]) + '\n'
            
                content += f"[Qualities{i}]\n"
                content += '\n'.join([f"Quality{j}={filters_data[j]['QValue']}" for j in range(1, len(filters_data) + 1)]) + '\n'
            
                if non_pk_filters_exist:
                    content += f"[Filters{i}]\n"
                    filters_not_pk = [f"Filter{j}={filter_type_mapping[filters_data[j]['FilterType']]}" for j in range(1, len(filters_data) + 1) if filters_data[j]['FilterType'] != 'PK']
                    content += '\n'.join(filters_not_pk) + '\n'


    # Write content to the .peace file
    with open(output_filename + ".peace", "w") as peace_file:
        peace_file.write(content)


# Function to open file explorer and update the corresponding entry field
def open_file_explorer(entry):
    file_path = filedialog.askopenfilename(title="Select EQ file", filetypes=[("Text Files", "*.txt")])
    entry.delete(0, tk.END)
    entry.insert(0, file_path)

message_colors = ["blue", "green"]
color_index = 0
message_label = None

# Function to handle the conversion
def convert_files():
    global color_index
    global message_label
    output_filename = output_filename_entry.get() or "output"
    comment = comment_entry.get() or "Generated 7.1 surround sound preset"
    paths = [entry.get() or "None" for entry in entry_fields]

    generate_peace_file(paths, output_filename, comment)
    
    # Clear the previous completion message, if exists
    if message_label is not None:
        message_label.destroy()
    
    # Add a message on the GUI to inform the user that the file generation is complete
    message_label = tk.Label(root, text="File generation completed!", fg=message_colors[color_index])
    message_label.pack()

    # Update the color index for the next message
    color_index = (color_index + 1) % len(message_colors)
    
# Creating the main application window
root = tk.Tk()
root.title("EQ File Converter")

# List to store entry fields and their respective names
entry_fields = []
field_names = ["All", "Left", "Right", "Center", "Subwoofer", "Left Rear", "Right Rear", "Left Side", "Right Side"]

# Function to create file input fields with respective names
def create_file_input(name):
    frame = tk.Frame(root)
    frame.pack()
    label = tk.Label(frame, text=f"{name}:")
    label.pack(side=tk.LEFT)
    entry = tk.Entry(frame, width=50)
    entry.pack(side=tk.LEFT)
    entry_fields.append(entry)
    browse_button = tk.Button(frame, text="Browse", command=lambda: open_file_explorer(entry))
    browse_button.pack(side=tk.LEFT)

# Create file input fields with respective names
for name in field_names:
    create_file_input(name)
    
# Entry field for the output file name
output_filename_label = tk.Label(root, text="Output File Name:")
output_filename_label.pack()
output_filename_entry = tk.Entry(root, width=50)
output_filename_entry.pack()

# Entry field for the comment
comment_label = tk.Label(root, text="Comment for Output File:")
comment_label.pack()
comment_entry = tk.Entry(root, width=50)
comment_entry.pack()

# Button to trigger the conversion process
convert_button = tk.Button(root, text="Convert Files", command=convert_files)
convert_button.pack()

# Run the application
root.mainloop()

from math import ceil


def to_encrypt_6(s, key): #прямая изгородь
    answer = [''] * key
    dir = 1
    cur = 0
    for e in s:
        answer[cur] += e
        cur += dir
        if cur == 0 or cur == key - 1:
            dir *= -1
    return ''.join(answer)


def to_encrypt_7(s, key): #обратная изгородь
    answer = [''] * key
    dir = -1
    cur = key - 1
    for e in s:
        answer[cur] += e
        cur += dir
        if cur == 0 or cur == key - 1:
            dir *= -1
    return ''.join(answer)


def to_encrypt_8(s, key): #перестановочная прямая
    key = sorted([(key[i], i) for i in range(len(key))])
    answ = ''
    mx = []
    for i in range(0, len(s), len(key)):
        mx.append(s[i:i + len(key)])
    for e in mx:
        for ind in key:
            if ind[1] < len(e):
                answ += e[ind[1]]
    return answ


def to_encrypt_9(s, key): #перестановочная обратная
    key = sorted([(key[i], i) for i in range(len(key))])
    mx = [''] * ceil(len(s) / len(key))
    cur = len(mx) - 1
    for i in range(0, len(s), len(key)):
        mx[cur] = s[i:i + len(key)][::-1]
        if len(mx[cur]) < len(key):
            mx[cur] = '0' * (len(key) - len(mx[cur])) + mx[cur]
        cur -= 1
    answ = ''
    for e in mx:
        for ind in key:
            if e[ind[1]] != '0':
                answ += e[ind[1]]
    return answ


def to_encrypt_10(s, key): #redefence прямой
    answer = [''] * len(key)
    dir = 1
    cur = 0
    for e in s:
        answer[cur] += e
        cur += dir
        if cur == 0 or cur == len(key) - 1:
            dir *= -1
    key = sorted([(key[i], i) for i in range(len(key))])
    redefence = ''
    for e in key:
        redefence += answer[e[1]]
    return redefence


def to_encrypt_11(s, key): #redefence обратный
    answer = [''] * len(key)
    dir = -1
    cur = len(key) - 1
    for e in s:
        answer[cur] += e
        cur += dir
        if cur == 0 or cur == len(key) - 1:
            dir *= -1
    key = sorted([(key[i], i) for i in range(len(key))])
    redefence = ''
    for e in key:
        redefence += answer[e[1]]
    return redefence


print(to_encrypt_6('изгородь', 3))
print(to_encrypt_7('изгородь', 3))
print(to_encrypt_8('перестановка', 'слово'))
print(to_encrypt_9('перестановка', 'слово'))
print(to_encrypt_10('изгородь', 'сон'))
print(to_encrypt_11('изгородь', 'сон'))

title: Advent of Code 2023 (Python) - Day 1
content:
total_part1 = 0
total_part2 = 0

digit_words = {'one':'1', 'two':'2', 'three':'3', 'four':'4', 'five':'5', 'six':'6',
'seven':'7', 'eight':'8', 'nine':'9'}

with open('input.txt', 'r') as f:
    for line in f.readlines():
        # part 1
        digits = [char for char in line.strip() if char.isdigit()]
        calib = int(digits[0] + digits[-1])
        total_part1 += calib

        # part 2
        s = line.strip()

        # first digit
        first_digit = None
        for i in range(len(s)):
            if s[i].isdigit():
                first_digit = s[i]
                break
            for word in digit_words:
                if s[i:].startswith(word):
                    first_digit = digit_words[word]
                    break
            if first_digit:
                break

        # last digit
        last_digit = None
        for i in range(len(s)-1, -1, -1):
            if s[i].isdigit():
                last_digit = s[i]
                break
            for word in digit_words:
                if s[i:].startswith(word):
                    last_digit = digit_words[word]
                    break
            if last_digit:
                break

        calib = int(first_digit + last_digit)
        total_part2 += calib

# part 1
print(total_part1)

# part 2
print(total_part2)

import random
from PIL import Image

def scramble_image(input_path, output_path, column_width, row_height):
    original_image = Image.open(input_path)  # open original image
    width, height = original_image.size  # image dimensions

    if column_width > width:
        print("Error : column_width is greater than image size")
        exit(-1)

    if row_height > height:
        print("Error : row_height is greater than image size")
        exit(-1)

    # calculation of the colum width


    # calculation of the padding
    padding_width = 0
    padding_height = 0
    if width % column_width:
        padding_width = column_width - (width % column_width)
        # recalculate the number of col

    if height % row_height:
        padding_height = row_height - (height % row_height)
        # recalculate the number of row

    print("will add " + str(padding_width) + " px in width")
    print("will split into " + str(padding_height) + " px in height")

    padded_image = Image.new("RGB", (width + padding_width, height + padding_height), "white")
    padded_image.paste(original_image, ((padding_width // 2), (padding_height // 2)))
    reversed_image = padded_image.transpose(Image.FLIP_LEFT_RIGHT).transpose(Image.FLIP_TOP_BOTTOM)
    reversed_image.save(input_path.removesuffix(".pgn") + "_Framework.png")

    new_width, new_height = reversed_image.size  # image dimensions
    num_columns = new_width // column_width
    num_row = new_height // row_height

    print("will split into " + str(num_columns) + " columns")
    print("will split into " + str(num_row) + " row")
    print("will split into " + str(num_row*num_columns) + " sub images")

    # image division
    sections = []
    for i in range(0, num_columns):  # use column_width as the step size
        for j in range(0, num_row):  # use column_height as the step size
            box = (i * column_width, j * row_height, (i + 1) * column_width, (j + 1) * row_height)
            section = reversed_image.crop(box)
            sections.append(section)
    random.shuffle(sections)  # sections shuffle

    # reorganisation of shuffled sections in a new scrambled image
    scrambled_image = Image.new("RGB", (new_width, new_height), "white")
    current_width = 0
    current_height = 0

    for section in sections:
        scrambled_image.paste(section, (current_width, current_height))
        current_height += row_height  # Use column_height for vertical positioning
        if current_height >= new_height:
            current_height = 0
            current_width += column_width
    # save scrambled image
    scrambled_image.save(output_path)


# Exemple d'utilisation
scramble_image("./Lenna.png", "./Lenna.scramble.png", 12, 10)
